==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: dice
<hw>dice</hw> <pr>(d⟦imac⟧s)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it> of
<plw>Die</plw>.</plu> <def>Small cubes used in gaming or in determining
by chance; also, the game played with dice. See <er>Die</er>,
<pos>n.</pos></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>dice coal</b></col>, <cd>a kind of coal easily splitting
into cubical fragments.</cd> <rj><au>Brande & C.</au></rj> </cs> <--
Illustr. of Dice. -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>dice</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: dice
<hw>dice</hw> <pr>(d⟦imac⟧s)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
